        "id": 398795,
        "name": null,
        "username": "Darkflame",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forum.magicball.net/darkflame/{size}/24_2.png",
        "created_at": "2014-10-30T01:11:25.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>This is a crazy idea.<br>\nI like it <img src=\"//forum.magicball.net/plugins/discourse-lba-emoji/images/takam/stuck_out_tongue.png?v=12\" title=\":stuck_out_tongue:\" class=\"emoji emoji-custom\" alt=\":stuck_out_tongue:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>\n<p>The other possibility I guess is to look if you can disable movement and fix the camera in the 3d scenes - effectively turning the 3d environments just into still backgrounds.<br>\nOf course, youd then have to do visual novels only set in the games locations, but it might be easier to get the dialogue working at least.</p>",
